All block-level elements with unspecified size will take the full available width.

If you add some css to the fieldset to set it to display as an inline block, it will not go full width. You can also set a width there is you wanted.

    fieldset{
      display: inline-block;
    }

or

    fieldset{
      width: 50%
    }


The only issue you might have here is that the fieldset might not flow properly because it&#39;ll be inline. You could also set a width on the fieldset using CSS or wrap the fieldset in a div and set the DIVs width to whatever width you need.

Here&#39;s a codepen with examples of each: https://codepen.io/jamiecalder/pen/dyyYLVp

